# Audio_Design

## 1. Applies when
Games with deliberate audio direction, sound effects, voice-over, ambient soundscapes, or music systems.

## 2. This document owns
Audio direction and sonic identity.
Sound effect specifications and implementation notes.
Voice-over casting, recording, and integration guidelines.
Ambient audio and environmental soundscapes.
Music system design (dynamic, layered, adaptive).
Audio middleware and toolchain decisions.
Mixing, mastering, and platform-specific audio targets.

## 3. This document does NOT own
Narrative dialogue content (→ Narrative_Script).
Cutscene direction or timing (→ Narrative_Pipeline).
UI sound triggers (→ UI_UX_Design).
Technical audio implementation details (→ Technical_Design, for engine-level audio pipeline).

## 4. Recommended chapter structure
1. Audio Direction & Sonic Identity · 2. Sound Effects (SFX) · 3. Voice-Over (VO) ·
4. Ambient & Environmental Audio · 5. Music System · 6. Audio Middleware & Toolchain ·
7. Mixing, Mastering & Platform Targets

## 5. Common boundaries
- Audio owns "what it sounds like"; Script owns "what is said".
- Music system behavior belongs here; music asset lists may live in a production tracker.
- Platform-specific audio constraints (memory, channels) belong here or in Technical_Design.

## 6. Common audit rules
- Check that VO guidelines reference Narrative_Script for dialogue content.
- Check that music system references narrative pacing from Narrative_Pipeline.
